1
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:15,455
Target bearing 0-2-0.

2
00:01:15,455 --> 00:01:17,439
Contact 0-2-0.

3
00:01:17,439 --> 00:01:20,764
- Range 20,000.
- Range 20,000 yards.

4
00:01:20,764 --> 00:01:24,725
- Course 2-5-5.
- Course 2-5-5 true.

5
00:01:24,725 --> 00:01:28,158
- Speed 13.
- Speed 13 knots.

6
00:01:28,158 --> 00:01:30,492
Cowboys.

7
00:01:59,745 --> 00:02:03,422
Man the guns.

8
00:02:31,715 --> 00:02:34,366
Enchanter, Mobile.

9
00:02:36,611 --> 00:02:40,059
Well, we're a long way from home.
Wake them up!

10
00:03:04,643 --> 00:03:08,669
Enchanter!
This is the US Coast Guard!

11
00:03:08,669 --> 00:03:11,803
Heave to and prepare to be boarded!

12
00:03:25,092 --> 00:03:29,150
Enchanter! You are a US flagged ship,
and we are going to board you.

13
00:03:29,508 --> 00:03:31,450
Heave to now!

14
00:03:42,468 --> 00:03:45,468
l want to see your crew on the bow.

15
00:04:00,837 --> 00:04:03,968
You two, move forward.

16
00:04:03,968 --> 00:04:06,336
Randall, come with me.

17
00:04:11,109 --> 00:04:14,524
- What do you want?
- Kneel down.

18
00:04:17,765 --> 00:04:21,922
Captain... Captain?

19
00:04:21,922 --> 00:04:23,514
Go ahead, Senior Chief.

20
00:04:24,325 --> 00:04:29,148
lt's a bad one. l think you'd better
send over the video camera.

21
00:04:46,118 --> 00:04:48,388
Jack, come on in.

22
00:04:50,822 --> 00:04:53,888
- How high is the pile on your desk?
- About this high.

23
00:04:53,888 --> 00:04:56,443
- Now it's this high.
- What have you got?

24
00:04:56,443 --> 00:05:01,404
You heard about that business in
the south Caribbean? l need the details.

25
00:05:01,404 --> 00:05:03,779
- By when?
- As soon as you can.

26
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:08,289
- OK.
- Jack? Be discreet.

27
00:05:10,247 --> 00:05:12,516
What do you mean?

28
00:05:12,516 --> 00:05:14,534
You will find out.

29
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:18,401
Mysterious...

30
00:05:20,071 --> 00:05:21,894
l love a mystery.

31
00:05:25,991 --> 00:05:28,925
- Ryan, John P.
- Let him through.

32
00:05:31,271 --> 00:05:33,759
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

33
00:05:33,759 --> 00:05:37,342
- You know where you're going?
- Yes. Thank you.

34
00:05:37,342 --> 00:05:41,668
- Oh, where do l park?
- Right over there.

35
00:05:52,072 --> 00:05:54,210
...main passageway, going forward...

36
00:05:54,210 --> 00:05:57,093
...master stateroom...
blood on the deck...

37
00:05:57,093 --> 00:06:00,835
19 cartridges were recovered...

38
00:06:00,835 --> 00:06:06,368
...as well as
the two weapons that fired them.

39
00:06:06,368 --> 00:06:12,996
The blood samples taken were
consistent with the crew, Hardin...

40
00:06:12,996 --> 00:06:16,477
...and his wife
and his son and daughter.

41
00:06:18,473 --> 00:06:20,894
...blood on sheets and pillows...

42
00:06:20,894 --> 00:06:25,407
...on both starboard and port side racks.
And on the mirror too.

43
00:06:25,407 --> 00:06:30,366
They were killed in their staterooms,
apparently as they slept.

44
00:06:30,366 --> 00:06:32,773
Dragged topside and thrown overboard.

45
00:06:34,217 --> 00:06:39,006
The two men in custody surrendered
after a brief attempt to escape.

46
00:06:39,006 --> 00:06:42,308
What do we know about them?
The men in custody?

47
00:06:44,906 --> 00:06:48,615
Half a dozen arrests for drug
trafficking in Bogota, Mr President.

48
00:06:49,769 --> 00:06:51,046
Drugs.

49
00:06:53,034 --> 00:06:56,165
Suspected ties to the Cali cartel,
not Medellin...

50
00:06:56,165 --> 00:06:57,672
You all right, James?

51
00:06:57,672 --> 00:06:59,874
...according to DEA.

52
00:06:59,874 --> 00:07:02,562
- Why?
- Nothing exotic, sir.

53
00:07:02,562 --> 00:07:05,763
Straight piracy and murder.
lt's not the first time.

54
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:11,174
lt's the first time it was a friend of mine.

55
00:07:12,874 --> 00:07:14,881
Yes, sir.

56
00:07:21,035 --> 00:07:24,330
- What was that? You all right?
- Yeah.

57
00:07:24,330 --> 00:07:26,945
l haven't slept in 36 hours.
l make any sense?

58
00:07:26,945 --> 00:07:30,497
l don't know. What did you say?
Just kidding. Good job.

59
00:07:34,026 --> 00:07:39,209
- You should give diplomacy lessons.
- To call it as l see it is my job.

60
00:07:39,209 --> 00:07:42,535
- And he's yours.
- Wait for me.

61
00:07:46,539 --> 00:07:47,848
Shut the door.

62
00:07:51,723 --> 00:07:56,458
l promised the American people
l'd do something about the drug problem.

63
00:07:56,458 --> 00:07:58,506
You are.

64
00:07:58,506 --> 00:08:02,628
We support the Colombians' efforts
against the cartels...

65
00:08:02,628 --> 00:08:08,098
We have accomplished nothing. Do these
drug dealers think we're powerless?

66
00:08:08,098 --> 00:08:13,353
That they can keep doing this kind
of thing, and there's no response ever?

67
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:18,790
Are you suggesting
a course of action, sir?

68
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:24,520
The course of action l'd suggest
is a course of action l can't suggest.

69
00:08:38,445 --> 00:08:41,827
l am...not sure where that leaves us.

70
00:08:45,773 --> 00:08:49,385
These drug cartels represent
a clear and present danger

71
00:08:49,385 --> 00:08:53,095
to the national security
of the United States.

72
00:09:26,861 --> 00:09:30,091
Cortez, Cortez.. !

73
00:10:20,847 --> 00:10:22,789
That doesn't surprise me.

74
00:10:23,663 --> 00:10:27,012
- lt should at least concern you.
- What can they do?

75
00:10:27,012 --> 00:10:30,347
Come after me? Arrest me?

76
00:10:30,347 --> 00:10:32,584
You're scaring me.

77
00:10:34,063 --> 00:10:38,635
Will you stop long enough
for me to tell you something important?

78
00:10:41,168 --> 00:10:42,957
Thank you.

79
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:51,822
Listen... You pay me to counsel you,
and l am counselling you.

80
00:10:51,822 --> 00:10:55,596
l am keeping you alive with information.

81
00:10:55,596 --> 00:11:01,063
lf you disregard my counsel and keep
running your business like this,

82
00:11:01,063 --> 00:11:05,423
with your balls and not your head,
two things will happen.

83
00:11:06,256 --> 00:11:09,552
l will quit, and you will get killed.

84
00:11:20,465 --> 00:11:24,360
You forgot to tell me
about your scouting trip.

85
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:28,042
- No, l didn't.
- You made another contact. Who?

86
00:11:28,722 --> 00:11:31,788
Castro always asked me
about my sources.

87
00:11:31,788 --> 00:11:37,224
- l always gave him the same answer.
- Castro didn't pay you what l pay.

88
00:11:37,224 --> 00:11:40,689
This one will cost you nothing.

89
00:11:42,098 --> 00:11:43,821
A woman.

90
00:11:43,821 --> 00:11:47,149
You're using a woman.

91
00:11:52,978 --> 00:11:55,695
lt won't float.

92
00:11:56,882 --> 00:11:59,697
- John, what do you want? Toast?
- Waffles!

93
00:11:59,697 --> 00:12:03,240
- No time for waffles.
- Anybody seen my keys?

94
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:05,996
On the front hall table or in your pocket.

95
00:12:05,996 --> 00:12:09,097
- Where are my keys?
- Pancakes!

96
00:12:09,097 --> 00:12:12,649
- Toast, please!
- Thank you.

97
00:12:12,649 --> 00:12:15,818
- Bye, pal.
- Daddy. lt won't float!

98
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:21,737
lt's not supposed to float,
it's a submarine. lt goes under water.

99
00:12:24,339 --> 00:12:25,059
Hello?

100
00:12:28,146 --> 00:12:29,423
When?

101
00:12:31,763 --> 00:12:34,130
l thought l had the flu.

102
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:37,804
l'd still think so
if they weren't telling me otherwise.

103
00:12:39,795 --> 00:12:43,276
What are they telling you?

104
00:12:43,276 --> 00:12:49,160
Pancreatic cancer of an aggressive
nature, if l heard them right.

105
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:52,298
Well, what does it mean?

106
00:12:53,171 --> 00:12:55,593
l guess it means l am in big trouble.

107
00:12:56,243 --> 00:13:00,586
- l mean, can they operate, or...?
- Maybe.

108
00:13:00,586 --> 00:13:06,190
That's what they said, "maybe", which
sounds suspiciously like ''no'' to me.

109
00:13:06,190 --> 00:13:08,723
There's one of them now.

110
00:13:10,644 --> 00:13:13,960
Hey, l am not dead yet.

111
00:13:14,964 --> 00:13:20,049
l am in a hospital, which means
that l am not in my office,

112
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:22,154
which means
l don't know what's going on.

113
00:13:22,772 --> 00:13:25,227
- l need you there.
- Where?

114
00:13:25,227 --> 00:13:29,073
- ln my office, doing my job.
- Wait...

115
00:13:29,073 --> 00:13:32,585
l hate not knowing
what's going on, you know that.

116
00:13:32,585 --> 00:13:35,539
l wouldn't know how to do your job, sir.

117
00:13:35,539 --> 00:13:39,956
You have been around.
You have been to the White House.

118
00:13:39,956 --> 00:13:43,597
- Once. l hated it.
- No, you didn't.

119
00:13:44,821 --> 00:13:48,618
Want to know about politics
in Washington? Four words...

120
00:13:48,618 --> 00:13:50,447
''Watch your back, Jack.''

121
00:13:56,245 --> 00:14:01,483
Bobby, you should be the first to know,
or the third or fourth...

122
00:14:01,483 --> 00:14:04,720
Ryan is to be acting
Deputy Director of lntelligence.

123
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:10,123
lt will be a provisional appointment,
of course, until James recovers.

124
00:14:10,123 --> 00:14:13,807
You brief him
on our aid programme to Colombia.

125
00:14:13,807 --> 00:14:18,676
He has to talk the Oversight Committee
out of another 75 million dollars.

126
00:14:18,676 --> 00:14:22,067
And not make a complete fool
out of himself.

127
00:14:24,086 --> 00:14:26,159
What about the Hardin murders?

128
00:14:26,159 --> 00:14:29,774
l am on it. The President's calling
for a full-court press.

129
00:14:29,774 --> 00:14:34,732
So, you guys are going to be
working together hand in hand.

130
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,747
That's great.

131
00:14:52,535 --> 00:14:54,771
Margaret...

132
00:14:54,771 --> 00:14:58,677
- Why don't we leave all his things?
- OK.

133
00:15:10,199 --> 00:15:12,949
Ryan. l can't believe it!

134
00:15:12,949 --> 00:15:16,657
He's not a team player,
is that what you're saying?

135
00:15:16,657 --> 00:15:18,678
He's a Boy Scout.

136
00:15:19,607 --> 00:15:24,943
A goddamn Boy Scout. Believes in
loyalty, cleanliness and knot-tying.

137
00:15:24,943 --> 00:15:27,250
So leave him out of it.

138
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:31,158
He's the Deputy Director of
lntelligence. That will be tricky.

139
00:15:31,158 --> 00:15:33,807
What does he need to know?

140
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:39,693
Nothing. He needs to know nothing.
He's going to know nothing.

141
00:15:40,664 --> 00:15:42,868
l want a copy
of the President's authorisation

142
00:15:42,868 --> 00:15:45,901
of this new action against the cartels.

143
00:15:46,872 --> 00:15:50,352
- You want what?
- You heard me.

144
00:15:51,705 --> 00:15:53,166
He doesn't know about it.

145
00:15:55,224 --> 00:16:01,007
Let me explain it to you very simply.
This is your deal. Not mine.

146
00:16:01,007 --> 00:16:05,998
Unless l have written authorisation,
this thing is over before it begins.

147
00:16:05,998 --> 00:16:11,025
l am not going to be the only one left
without a chair when the music stops.

148
00:16:50,138 --> 00:16:53,553
Reciprocity. That's a clever name for it.

149
00:16:53,553 --> 00:16:57,748
Revenge is a very, very,
very dangerous motivation.

150
00:16:59,610 --> 00:17:05,274
Are you able to handle this operation
or not? l am looking for a yes or no.

151
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:08,282
You're looking for a political mess.

152
00:17:08,282 --> 00:17:11,126
- Yes or no?
- ls that what they want?

153
00:17:11,126 --> 00:17:15,568
They want what every first-term
administration wants. A second term.

154
00:17:17,051 --> 00:17:20,117
l don't imagine the boys on the Hill
have approved this.

155
00:17:25,723 --> 00:17:27,349
Have they?

156
00:17:29,435 --> 00:17:31,290
ls that a ''no''?

157
00:17:37,147 --> 00:17:39,286
Shit.

158
00:17:39,286 --> 00:17:45,015
l want the money in my account
before l move an inch.

159
00:17:45,015 --> 00:17:48,343
- You got it.
- l need a ComSat link.

160
00:17:48,343 --> 00:17:50,744
- An insertion team.
- Have a brigade.

161
00:17:50,744 --> 00:17:55,283
l don't want a brigade. Just 12 men
who understand discretionary warfare.

162
00:17:55,283 --> 00:17:59,097
- Special Ops people, Spanish-speaking.
- Cutter will get the military.

163
00:18:05,852 --> 00:18:08,405
- How are you today, sir?
- Very well.

164
00:18:08,405 --> 00:18:11,606
- The purpose of your visit?
- Business.

165
00:18:11,606 --> 00:18:14,391
- What business are you in?
- l sell tractors.

166
00:18:14,391 --> 00:18:16,379
l build them, then l sell them.

167
00:18:17,885 --> 00:18:21,682
- And how long will you be staying?
- A few days.

168
00:18:48,381 --> 00:18:51,927
l know it's a risk,
but what's the alternative?

169
00:18:51,927 --> 00:18:56,534
Zapping a retina with 6,000 rads
of cobalt? Not a pretty picture.

170
00:18:56,534 --> 00:18:59,604
Prettier than a tumour
spreading in the cranial sack.

171
00:18:59,604 --> 00:19:01,716
What is her name?

172
00:19:04,189 --> 00:19:07,353
Listen... Hungry?

173
00:19:07,353 --> 00:19:11,446
- Starved.
- We could forget about lunch.

174
00:19:11,446 --> 00:19:16,218
- We did that last time, remember?
- Do l remember? Do you?

175
00:19:17,982 --> 00:19:21,527
- Vaguely.
- Maybe l should refresh your memory.

176
00:19:23,742 --> 00:19:26,677
- Maybe you should.
- Your table is ready now.

177
00:19:26,677 --> 00:19:29,716
- We don't need it. l will get a cab.
- Moira?

178
00:19:29,716 --> 00:19:35,157
- Hi! How are you? How's Jack?
- He's great, just great.

179
00:19:35,157 --> 00:19:38,196
- You still with the FBl?
- The Director's office.

180
00:19:38,196 --> 00:19:40,855
- Who was that?
- My new friend.

181
00:19:40,855 --> 00:19:43,870
Señor Roberto Landa.

182
00:19:43,870 --> 00:19:47,926
- Doesn't he look like Jack?
- Does he? l can't quite see.

183
00:19:47,926 --> 00:19:52,470
- Only Latin.
- A Latin Jack? This l have to see.

184
00:19:53,471 --> 00:19:55,838
l have to go. Bye.

185
00:19:57,727 --> 00:20:02,005
Well, we know it's not piracy.
Pirates steal boats.

186
00:20:02,655 --> 00:20:06,965
They had plane tickets to Bogota
the morning after the killings.

187
00:20:06,965 --> 00:20:08,663
- Hey, Dan.
- How's it going?

188
00:20:08,663 --> 00:20:12,061
We're sneaking up on a motive.
Dan Murray, FBl.

189
00:20:12,061 --> 00:20:15,006
- Ralph Williams, DEA.
- Said anything yet?

190
00:20:15,006 --> 00:20:19,391
- Yeah, ''We're innocent.''
- Till the D.A. offers them a deal.

191
00:20:19,391 --> 00:20:22,868
He already has. Regular or extra crispy.

192
00:20:22,868 --> 00:20:26,204
Either referring to fried chicken
or the electric chair.

193
00:20:26,976 --> 00:20:28,983
Are you picturing a hit?

194
00:20:28,983 --> 00:20:33,375
On a respectable American
businessman and his family?

195
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,891
You're assuming he's respectable.

196
00:20:44,961 --> 00:20:50,460
We have memos,
letters, credit card statements...

197
00:20:50,460 --> 00:20:55,775
...phone bills, everything
you could need to break his code.

198
00:20:55,775 --> 00:20:58,937
- What's this?
- Old high school yearbook.

199
00:20:58,937 --> 00:21:02,934
- Sweethearts, football team...
- You think?

200
00:21:02,934 --> 00:21:07,612
- l don't know.
- OK, let's see what we have got.

201
00:21:07,612 --> 00:21:10,013
- No cream?
- There wasn't any.

202
00:21:10,754 --> 00:21:14,583
Let's start with birthdays.
Bet your ATM code is your birthday.

203
00:21:14,583 --> 00:21:17,623
- Close.
- ln reverse?

204
00:21:19,234 --> 00:21:21,536
All right, his birthday is...

205
00:21:22,945 --> 00:21:28,128
That would be too easy, wouldn't it?
Try it in reverse.

206
00:21:28,128 --> 00:21:30,810
No. His wife's?

207
00:21:31,906 --> 00:21:33,433
No. His son's?

208
00:21:33,433 --> 00:21:35,773
- This could take...
- Months.

209
00:21:35,773 --> 00:21:37,760
Son's in reverse. This is for you.

210
00:21:40,322 --> 00:21:43,191
No. Wife's in reverse.

211
00:21:43,191 --> 00:21:45,337
No. Daughter's in reverse.

212
00:21:45,337 --> 00:21:48,376
You have got to change your ATM code.

213
00:21:55,619 --> 00:21:56,895
l got it!

214
00:21:57,315 --> 00:21:59,005
l got it!

215
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:12,892
Wife's birth month,
daughter's day, son's year.

216
00:22:12,892 --> 00:22:15,808
But not in reverse. Sorry.

217
00:22:22,915 --> 00:22:26,046
Print me out that one, will you?

218
00:22:26,046 --> 00:22:28,219
Good boy.

219
00:22:28,219 --> 00:22:32,763
Three years ago, Hardin received
a large infusion of foreign money,

220
00:22:32,763 --> 00:22:37,950
which he invested wisely
in 20 major shopping centres in the US.

221
00:22:37,950 --> 00:22:42,394
l say wisely because in the middle of
the recession, he posted record profits.

222
00:22:42,394 --> 00:22:46,753
At least to the lRS, who he apparently
feared more than his own partners.

223
00:22:46,753 --> 00:22:49,501
According to the figures he gave them...

224
00:22:51,172 --> 00:22:54,205
...the shopping centres
weren't doing so well.

225
00:22:54,205 --> 00:22:58,780
But he was just skimming most of
the profits, 650 million dollars,

226
00:22:58,780 --> 00:23:02,745
and putting it in numbered accounts
in Luxembourg, Panama

227
00:23:02,745 --> 00:23:07,652
and the Cayman lslands.
They killed him for it.

228
00:23:07,652 --> 00:23:08,652
Who?

229
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:12,864
- His partners.
- Who were his partners?

230
00:23:12,864 --> 00:23:19,259
lt seems clear that he was laundering
money for the Colombian drug cartels.

231
00:23:19,259 --> 00:23:25,212
Jesus... l knew the man for 40 years.
We went to school together.

232
00:23:25,829 --> 00:23:28,317
We almost went into business together.

233
00:23:28,317 --> 00:23:31,420
That would have been good.

234
00:23:32,453 --> 00:23:35,323
The press is going
to have a field-day with this.

235
00:23:35,323 --> 00:23:39,966
- No one outside this room knows.
- They will. They always do.

236
00:23:39,966 --> 00:23:44,836
lt will come out, you're right about that.
And when it does, we will...

237
00:23:44,836 --> 00:23:49,635
...downplay your relationship
with Hardin somehow.

238
00:23:51,654 --> 00:23:53,279
- What?
- What?

239
00:23:53,279 --> 00:23:57,024
- We will defuse it.
- Do you disagree?

240
00:23:57,024 --> 00:23:57,774
No.

241
00:23:59,046 --> 00:24:03,781
Well, actually, yes.
l would go in the other direction.

242
00:24:03,781 --> 00:24:08,798
lf a reporter asked if you and Hardin
were friends, l'd say ''good friends''.

243
00:24:08,798 --> 00:24:13,505
lf they asked if you were good friends,
l'd say ''lifelong friends''.

244
00:24:13,505 --> 00:24:19,005
Give them no place to go,
nothing to report. No story.

245
00:24:21,094 --> 00:24:25,764
l mean, it's no sense in
defusing a bomb after it's already...

246
00:24:27,047 --> 00:24:29,567
...it's already gone off.

247
00:24:52,039 --> 00:24:54,211
- Damn.
- Shit.

248
00:24:55,463 --> 00:24:56,740
Do you see him?

249
00:24:57,960 --> 00:25:01,604
All right. Move your team
two metres to the left.

250
00:25:04,968 --> 00:25:07,651
That's it. Stop.

251
00:25:07,651 --> 00:25:11,678
Touch that light-coloured grass.
Sniper at your feet.

252
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:14,687
Nothing here, Sergeant Major.

253
00:25:15,112 --> 00:25:17,829
- Damn!
- He is good.

254
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:38,081
That was close.
How's he moving so fast?

255
00:25:42,761 --> 00:25:46,536
l see him. Come in.
Straight in. Now. Run!

256
00:25:48,009 --> 00:25:50,016
Keep coming.

257
00:25:51,561 --> 00:25:55,555
To your left. To your left.

258
00:25:56,745 --> 00:26:00,127
And stop. Sniper at your feet.

259
00:26:02,057 --> 00:26:03,431
What is it?

260
00:26:07,273 --> 00:26:08,735
He had lunch here.

261
00:26:09,929 --> 00:26:14,664
McDonald's quarter-pounder
with cheese.

262
00:26:15,114 --> 00:26:16,364
Damn.

263
00:26:22,378 --> 00:26:25,193
- Damn!
- That's four.

264
00:26:26,058 --> 00:26:29,767
All right, you won this one.
Come on out!

265
00:26:31,562 --> 00:26:34,529
Soldier, how did you get
that close to me?

266
00:26:34,529 --> 00:26:39,816
Sniper approached instructor by being
a sneaky bastard, Sergeant Major!

267
00:26:39,816 --> 00:26:43,972
Do you know the fine for littering
in California, Chavez?

268
00:26:43,972 --> 00:26:46,309
Yes, sir!

269
00:26:48,842 --> 00:26:52,421
l saw you on the sniper course.
You looked good.

270
00:26:52,421 --> 00:26:55,969
- Just about finished here, Sergeant?
- Yes, sir.

271
00:26:55,969 --> 00:26:59,751
Looking forward to taking
some leave with your wife and kids?

272
00:27:00,747 --> 00:27:04,424
- Don't have any wife or kids, sir.
- What do you have?

273
00:27:05,323 --> 00:27:11,586
You don't call anybody often,
you don't write or receive many letters.

274
00:27:14,283 --> 00:27:16,739
Who are you, sir, if l may ask?

275
00:27:16,739 --> 00:27:21,283
Mr Clark and l are putting together
a mission. My team is a part of it.

276
00:27:21,995 --> 00:27:26,185
You will be gone up to six months,
after which, if you're not dead,

277
00:27:26,185 --> 00:27:29,828
you will have a choice
of assignments in Special Ops.

278
00:27:45,516 --> 00:27:50,219
...defusing an issue that was
snowballing into another scandal.

279
00:27:50,956 --> 00:27:54,982
The New York Times is reporting that
you and Hardin were good friends?

280
00:27:54,982 --> 00:27:59,109
No, not good friends.
We were lifelong friends.

281
00:27:59,109 --> 00:28:02,986
l said that. l said that.

282
00:28:05,036 --> 00:28:06,727
l told him to say that.

283
00:28:07,341 --> 00:28:10,985
- What?
- l didn't say anything.

284
00:28:10,985 --> 00:28:14,498
- But you were thinking something.
- No.

285
00:28:14,498 --> 00:28:18,826
l was just distracted by the trouble
you were having with your ensemble.

286
00:28:20,365 --> 00:28:24,937
Well, it's not every day
you have to look trustworthy.

287
00:28:24,937 --> 00:28:28,298
- Who told who to say what?
- lt's not important.

288
00:28:29,774 --> 00:28:32,556
- The President?
- Yeah.

289
00:28:32,556 --> 00:28:36,744
Mom says she makes more money
than the President.

290
00:28:36,744 --> 00:28:39,757
She's probably right. Bye.

291
00:28:48,078 --> 00:28:52,105
Thank you, Dr Ryan,
for the information you have shared with us.

292
00:28:53,166 --> 00:28:56,298
- Thank you, Senator.
- We must help the Colombians

293
00:28:56,298 --> 00:29:00,773
in their struggle to curtail
the drug cartels' activities.

294
00:29:00,773 --> 00:29:06,987
However, l am confused.
How do you see additional funds alone

295
00:29:06,987 --> 00:29:09,867
advancing this programme
from the failure that it is?

296
00:29:09,867 --> 00:29:14,154
- You see what l am getting at?
- No, l am afraid l don't.

297
00:29:14,154 --> 00:29:17,580
You said this effort would be
totally benign on our part.

298
00:29:17,580 --> 00:29:22,565
The finding clearly states our assistance
is limited to supply and advice only.

299
00:29:22,565 --> 00:29:24,077
l have read that.

300
00:29:24,077 --> 00:29:28,844
l have also read a similar finding
written 35 years ago

301
00:29:28,844 --> 00:29:32,936
regarding a little-thought-of
sliver of jungle in south-east Asia.

302
00:29:32,936 --> 00:29:39,049
Sorry, you're comparing our request
for anti-drug funds to Vietnam?

303
00:29:39,049 --> 00:29:43,044
l am comparing it to every time
a committee such as this is asked

304
00:29:43,044 --> 00:29:47,471
to render judgement
based on less than all the facts.

305
00:29:50,416 --> 00:29:53,133
l am afraid l don't know
what to say to that.

306
00:29:53,133 --> 00:29:56,362
You could assure us
we have been given all the facts.

307
00:29:56,362 --> 00:29:58,284
l thought l had.

308
00:29:58,284 --> 00:30:03,631
You could further assure us, then,
that this increase in funds

309
00:30:03,631 --> 00:30:07,054
will not be used for
any covert military action.

310
00:30:07,824 --> 00:30:10,923
l don't know how you're getting to this.

311
00:30:10,923 --> 00:30:14,122
Long experience, sir.

312
00:30:14,122 --> 00:30:15,914
No troops, then?

313
00:30:15,914 --> 00:30:21,710
l enunciate that clearly because
l don't want there to be any mistake.

314
00:30:21,710 --> 00:30:23,334
No troops.

315
00:30:24,369 --> 00:30:27,086
You could say l have your word on that?

316
00:30:27,086 --> 00:30:29,704
You could indeed, because you do.

317
00:30:44,753 --> 00:30:50,983
Listen up! Dog tags...
Take them off, pass them forward.

318
00:30:50,983 --> 00:30:56,620
Check your pockets for anything
that can be used for identification.

319
00:31:04,242 --> 00:31:05,518
We're feet dry.

320
00:31:18,994 --> 00:31:22,028
Landing zone in sight. Get ready.

321
00:31:22,028 --> 00:31:24,943
Good luck, boys. Go get them.

322
00:31:28,722 --> 00:31:30,795
OK, let's take her down now.

323
00:33:13,525 --> 00:33:14,802
Hey, Bob.

324
00:33:17,174 --> 00:33:19,345
- How you doing?
- Good, sir.

325
00:33:20,629 --> 00:33:22,352
Good to see you.

326
00:33:28,213 --> 00:33:31,475
- Morning, Jack.
- Ryan! Come on in.

327
00:33:32,118 --> 00:33:34,289
- Do you know everyone?
- Yes, yes.

328
00:33:34,289 --> 00:33:37,520
- Coffee? Bagel?
- Coffee. Black, please.

329
00:33:38,678 --> 00:33:41,940
- How's the family?
- Good, sir.

330
00:33:41,940 --> 00:33:45,331
- When do l meet the other Dr Ryan?
- She's dying to meet you, sir.

331
00:33:45,331 --> 00:33:47,469
Good, good. Sit down.

332
00:33:53,975 --> 00:33:58,001
- The cash is still there?
- Sir?

333
00:33:58,001 --> 00:34:02,161
- ln Hardin's off-shore accounts.
- 650 million dollars.

334
00:34:02,161 --> 00:34:04,399
- And change.
- And change...

335
00:34:04,399 --> 00:34:07,862
- And we have the account numbers.
- Yes, sir.

336
00:34:07,862 --> 00:34:13,107
Well, what are we waiting for?
Let's get it.

337
00:34:13,107 --> 00:34:17,166
Let's turn this thing around.
650 million dollars and change.

338
00:34:17,166 --> 00:34:20,718
lt's worth ten times that
in political capital.

339
00:34:23,095 --> 00:34:24,345
What?

340
00:34:25,783 --> 00:34:32,941
Well... This connection between
Hardin and the cartels is a theory.

341
00:34:32,941 --> 00:34:35,413
- Theory?
- A theory of mine.

342
00:34:35,413 --> 00:34:39,285
- lt's a theory?
- Well, l know the money is there.

343
00:34:39,285 --> 00:34:43,921
But who exactly Hardin
was working for, l don't know.

344
00:34:43,921 --> 00:34:49,456
l think we would have to establish
that before we could seize the money.

345
00:34:52,344 --> 00:34:55,311
So go down there. Establish it.

346
00:34:55,311 --> 00:34:57,847
- Go where?
- Colombia.

347
00:34:59,961 --> 00:35:02,165
Who, me?

348
00:35:05,561 --> 00:35:10,133
l leave you alone for two weeks,
and you walk into a big bear trap.

349
00:35:10,133 --> 00:35:12,206
l don't know what l was thinking.

350
00:35:12,206 --> 00:35:18,422
You were thinking about impressing
the President. You shouldn't do that.

351
00:35:18,422 --> 00:35:21,749
- November.
- January.

352
00:35:21,749 --> 00:35:23,604
Of last year.

353
00:35:26,617 --> 00:35:30,992
There's a guy down there,
at least used to be... Clark.

354
00:35:31,929 --> 00:35:34,264
We go way back. Good man.

355
00:35:34,841 --> 00:35:37,230
lf you hit a brick wall, look him up.

356
00:35:38,202 --> 00:35:40,569
Admiral Greer?

357
00:35:40,569 --> 00:35:44,592
- Chemotherapy.
- Oh, shit.

358
00:35:44,592 --> 00:35:47,031
Here we go again.

359
00:35:48,218 --> 00:35:50,487
How's Ritter behaving?

360
00:35:50,487 --> 00:35:54,195
Ritter's Ritter. He's leaving me alone.

361
00:35:54,195 --> 00:35:58,388
Are you sure? Watch him like a hawk.

362
00:35:58,388 --> 00:36:00,943
- How are you feeling today?
- OK.

363
00:36:00,943 --> 00:36:06,416
We will get you in a room, give you
warm blankets, get you lying down.

364
00:36:06,416 --> 00:36:11,671
And then we will get you back
to your room and get you comfortable...

365
00:37:02,236 --> 00:37:05,367
Variable, this is Knife,
stand by to copy, over.

366
00:37:08,059 --> 00:37:11,126
Variable, this is Knife,
stand by to copy, over.

367
00:37:11,126 --> 00:37:15,154
Knife, this is Variable,
your signal is five by five, over.

368
00:37:18,461 --> 00:37:20,348
Clear.

369
00:37:43,068 --> 00:37:45,076
The chicken is in the pot. Over.

370
00:37:47,069 --> 00:37:49,719
- Cook it.
- Roger that.

371
00:38:05,790 --> 00:38:09,237
Honey? l am late.

372
00:38:10,654 --> 00:38:12,694
Have a good trip.

373
00:38:14,014 --> 00:38:16,599
l am not going to say it.

374
00:38:16,599 --> 00:38:17,319
Don't.

375
00:38:18,814 --> 00:38:20,952
Be careful.

376
00:38:47,263 --> 00:38:53,558
Local time is, well, actually, it's
the same as Washington, 11.16 a.m.

377
00:38:53,558 --> 00:38:57,076
Temperature is
69 degrees Fahrenheit...

378
00:39:03,423 --> 00:39:05,594
Doctor Ryan!

379
00:39:14,591 --> 00:39:18,006
DEA Special Agent Jean Fowler.
How you doing?

380
00:39:18,006 --> 00:39:20,215
- First time in Bogota?
- Yeah.

381
00:39:20,215 --> 00:39:24,759
Let's not stand here
and let someone take a shot at you.

382
00:39:40,704 --> 00:39:43,999
- And these two?
- They're brothers.

383
00:39:46,912 --> 00:39:50,840
Don't do that. Give Dr Ryan
a bit more air back here, please.

384
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:52,830
Bulletproof.

385
00:40:00,064 --> 00:40:03,709
We don't have a picture.
Escobedo's intelligence officer.

386
00:40:04,225 --> 00:40:06,745
We don't have a name either,
but we know he exists.

387
00:40:07,873 --> 00:40:10,524
The invisible man?

388
00:40:11,329 --> 00:40:13,784
Gently, gently. With your hands.

389
00:40:13,784 --> 00:40:16,986
Luis, put your hands together.

390
00:40:17,825 --> 00:40:20,509
No, your hands together!

391
00:40:23,425 --> 00:40:26,011
Luis, watch the canter!

392
00:40:27,074 --> 00:40:29,943
Yes, very good!

393
00:40:37,922 --> 00:40:40,540
We lost another plane.

394
00:40:47,074 --> 00:40:50,871
- Who is doing this?
- lf l had to guess...

395
00:40:50,871 --> 00:40:54,457
No, l did not ask you to guess.
l can guess.

396
00:40:56,066 --> 00:40:58,171
Someone's been talking
to the drug police.

397
00:40:58,171 --> 00:41:02,878
lmpossible. lf anyone spoke to the
police, l'd be the first to know.

398
00:41:02,878 --> 00:41:04,985
Ernesto!

399
00:41:06,627 --> 00:41:11,449
ls one of the others trying to ruin me,
after what l did to the American?

400
00:41:11,449 --> 00:41:16,921
l guess that wasn't quite
the deterrent you thought it would be.

401
00:41:16,921 --> 00:41:18,978
Find out who it is.

402
00:41:26,883 --> 00:41:29,022
What do you make of this, Colonel?

403
00:41:30,595 --> 00:41:32,188
An opportunity.

404
00:41:34,723 --> 00:41:36,731
An opportunity, Sipo.

405
00:41:50,532 --> 00:41:53,728
- Good afternoon.
- Messages, please?

406
00:41:55,492 --> 00:41:59,747
- Dr Ryan?
- Clark? Sorry l am late.

407
00:41:59,747 --> 00:42:02,079
l have got ten minutes.

408
00:42:04,356 --> 00:42:08,447
l am positive Hardin was tied into
the cartels. lt's drug money.

409
00:42:08,447 --> 00:42:12,060
- But you can't prove it.
- So far.

410
00:42:13,732 --> 00:42:16,962
- Mind if l ask you a question?
- No.

411
00:42:16,962 --> 00:42:23,105
Why are you telling me all this?
l have been out of the game for a long time.

412
00:42:25,061 --> 00:42:30,112
l was told that you were wired in,
that you knew the town, the people.

413
00:42:30,112 --> 00:42:33,625
- That you were a player.
- Who told you that?

414
00:42:35,429 --> 00:42:36,858
Jim Greer.

415
00:42:39,237 --> 00:42:40,514
How's he doing?

416
00:42:43,525 --> 00:42:45,827
He's not good.

417
00:42:47,205 --> 00:42:49,114
lt's cancer.

418
00:42:49,114 --> 00:42:51,227
Terminal.

419
00:42:53,350 --> 00:42:56,863
- He's a good man.
- The best.

420
00:43:03,398 --> 00:43:05,634
You a coffee drinker, Dr Ryan?

421
00:43:08,870 --> 00:43:12,482
- Yeah, l like coffee.
- Try the Lindo brand.

422
00:43:12,482 --> 00:43:15,875
- Lindo?
- l think you will like it.

423
00:43:21,798 --> 00:43:25,028
Mr president, l have got some good news.

424
00:43:25,028 --> 00:43:31,486
Hardin's partner here was someone
you may know of. Ernesto Escobedo.

425
00:43:31,486 --> 00:43:35,299
- Figures.
- ls this another of your theories?

426
00:43:35,974 --> 00:43:41,539
No, sir. We can call this one fact.
Escobedo, like every drug lord here,

427
00:43:41,539 --> 00:43:46,853
also had legitimate businesses.
Hardin was doing business with them.

428
00:43:47,431 --> 00:43:52,100
lmporting among other things,
coffee, which means nothing,

429
00:43:52,100 --> 00:43:58,493
but he was paying too much for
this coffee. 6,200 dollars a pound.

430
00:43:58,493 --> 00:44:02,046
- That's expensive coffee.
- l'd have to agree.

431
00:44:02,046 --> 00:44:04,933
This is good news. l think this does it.

432
00:44:05,543 --> 00:44:08,839
Sir, l also have some other news
which is not so good.

433
00:44:09,704 --> 00:44:11,231
Oh, God...

434
00:44:11,231 --> 00:44:17,248
The DEA feels that the government
here would want the seized funds.

435
00:44:17,248 --> 00:44:22,085
- Or at least a large portion.
- This is our money.

436
00:44:22,085 --> 00:44:25,892
- We found it.
- We could try telling them that.

437
00:44:25,892 --> 00:44:29,318
Try? Tell them.
Or don't tell them, l don't care.

438
00:44:29,928 --> 00:44:33,987
- Sir, with all due respect...
- This is our money, tell them that.

439
00:44:33,987 --> 00:44:39,008
l wouldn't know what to say
or where to start, l am not a negotiator.

440
00:44:39,008 --> 00:44:41,380
Don't you know someone there?

441
00:44:41,380 --> 00:44:44,162
l went to school
with their Attorney General.

442
00:44:44,162 --> 00:44:48,769
Jacobs will come down.
He will negotiate. This is our money.

443
00:44:49,897 --> 00:44:51,391
Thank...

444
00:44:52,553 --> 00:44:54,277
Thank you.

445
00:44:57,321 --> 00:45:00,136
l hate this job.

446
00:46:14,123 --> 00:46:16,228
Eyes up!

447
00:46:18,507 --> 00:46:20,394
Demo Team, up!

448
00:46:27,211 --> 00:46:29,383
Fire in the hole!

449
00:46:33,675 --> 00:46:37,385
Let's go, let's go!
Move out! Go, go, go!

450
00:46:57,804 --> 00:46:59,943
Whoever did this is dead.

451
00:47:01,484 --> 00:47:05,860
Whoever did this to me is dead!

452
00:47:05,860 --> 00:47:11,179
Do you hear me?
Are you listening to me?

453
00:47:24,877 --> 00:47:28,489
Mr Jacobs, could you sign these
before you leave?

454
00:47:29,645 --> 00:47:34,795
Moira... Why don't you
call in sick tomorrow?

455
00:47:34,795 --> 00:47:38,153
And the next day. l won't tell anybody.

456
00:47:38,153 --> 00:47:40,903
Even when you're not here,
there's plenty to do.

457
00:47:41,614 --> 00:47:45,094
- Your itinerary.
- You're arguing with me about this?

458
00:47:45,998 --> 00:47:49,991
You work too hard. Adios.

459
00:48:27,023 --> 00:48:29,740
- Landa & Landa.
- Roberto Landa, please.

460
00:48:29,740 --> 00:48:34,376
- This is Moira Wolfson.
- One moment, please.

461
00:48:34,376 --> 00:48:38,023
l think he's on the factory floor.

462
00:48:43,183 --> 00:48:46,478
- Yes?
- A Moira Wolfson is calling.

463
00:48:47,791 --> 00:48:52,647
l told her you were
on the factory floor. Go ahead.

464
00:48:52,647 --> 00:48:55,914
- Moira... !
- Hi.

465
00:48:55,914 --> 00:49:00,935
You free the next couple of days?
l am.

466
00:49:01,615 --> 00:49:05,991
My boss is leaving the country.

467
00:49:05,991 --> 00:49:11,048
- Can l call you later?
- All right, call me at home. Bye.

468
00:49:19,408 --> 00:49:25,256
Good afternoon.
Good news in the fight against drugs.

469
00:49:25,256 --> 00:49:29,002
An investigation
by the Department of Justice

470
00:49:29,585 --> 00:49:33,960
has identified several
bank accounts, from Luxembourg

471
00:49:33,960 --> 00:49:37,773
to the Cayman lslands,
used for laundering drug money

472
00:49:37,773 --> 00:49:43,021
on an unprecedented scale.
Working with five foreign governments,

473
00:49:43,021 --> 00:49:46,731
we have taken action
to seize those funds,

474
00:49:46,731 --> 00:49:50,345
which amount to
over 650 million dollars.

475
00:49:50,345 --> 00:49:52,040
Oh, shit.

476
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:56,552
Also to seize 20 real estate
joint venture investments in the US

