l will take care of the one that got away.

715
01:21:07,685 --> 01:21:12,474
Once Escobedo is gone,
l will be in a position to help you.

716
01:21:12,474 --> 01:21:16,671
- You want to help me?
- Your country. Your people.

717
01:21:16,671 --> 01:21:21,376
By restructuring the drug trade.
By regulating it.

718
01:21:22,693 --> 01:21:27,996
What would you say if l promised you
l'd halve cocaine shipments to the US?

719
01:21:29,574 --> 01:21:33,632
l'd say you'd been using
too much of your product.

720
01:21:33,632 --> 01:21:37,213
l can also give you regular quotas
on major arrests

721
01:21:37,213 --> 01:21:40,447
that your police can take credit for.

722
01:21:40,447 --> 01:21:44,160
lmagine. Dramatic seizures.
Drastic reductions.

723
01:21:44,160 --> 01:21:48,865
No more senseless violence.
You will have your victory.

724
01:21:53,095 --> 01:21:54,622
ln return for what?

725
01:21:55,878 --> 01:21:59,620
l also need a victory,
to establish my position

726
01:21:59,620 --> 01:22:04,255
with what is left of the cartel,
so l can help you.

727
01:22:04,967 --> 01:22:09,637
l need to defeat those soldiers
blowing up everything they see.

728
01:22:09,637 --> 01:22:15,331
Give me maps of their locations.
Cut off their communications.

729
01:22:22,087 --> 01:22:27,587
DEA's sending the audio
surveillance tape. l haven't got it yet.

730
01:22:30,119 --> 01:22:35,237
You know what you think about...
when you're lying here?

731
01:22:36,551 --> 01:22:39,585
You know you're going to die,
and you think...

732
01:22:41,480 --> 01:22:46,019
...that's all right. You lived a long time.

733
01:22:46,019 --> 01:22:48,191
You had a family that loved you.

734
01:22:48,583 --> 01:22:52,707
You had a job that you thought
made a difference.

735
01:22:53,576 --> 01:22:56,260
That you thought was honourable.

736
01:22:57,192 --> 01:22:59,876
And then you see this.

737
01:23:03,720 --> 01:23:07,430
l am afraid if l dig any deeper...

738
01:23:07,430 --> 01:23:10,080
...no one's going to like what l find.

739
01:23:15,689 --> 01:23:18,885
You took an oath...

740
01:23:18,885 --> 01:23:21,056
...if you recall...

741
01:23:23,785 --> 01:23:27,168
...when you first came to work for me.

742
01:23:27,168 --> 01:23:32,836
And l don't mean to the National
Security Advisor of the United States,

743
01:23:33,993 --> 01:23:37,125
l mean to his boss.

744
01:23:37,125 --> 01:23:39,678
And l don't mean the President.

745
01:23:41,257 --> 01:23:44,421
You gave your word to...

746
01:23:45,962 --> 01:23:48,449
...his boss.

747
01:23:48,449 --> 01:23:51,105
You gave your word...

748
01:23:51,105 --> 01:23:55,551
...to the people of the United States.

749
01:23:56,778 --> 01:23:59,461
Your word is who you are.

750
01:24:04,521 --> 01:24:05,983
What else have you got there?

751
01:24:12,010 --> 01:24:14,945
l brought you some new magazines.

752
01:24:24,074 --> 01:24:29,671
The situation in East Timor seems
to have stabilised during the day.

753
01:24:29,671 --> 01:24:33,479
- ls that it?
- Except for the other thing.

754
01:24:34,890 --> 01:24:37,825
We have accomplished a lot,
we're seeing tangible results.

755
01:24:37,825 --> 01:24:41,573
Drug shipments are down.
The price on the street is rising.

756
01:24:41,573 --> 01:24:45,994
The administration is perceived
to be doing something right.

757
01:24:45,994 --> 01:24:49,002
What's the bad news?

758
01:24:50,700 --> 01:24:56,101
l am worried about the car bomb coming
so soon after Jacobs' assassination.

759
01:24:57,899 --> 01:25:00,518
Just the kind of thing reporters live for.

760
01:25:00,518 --> 01:25:04,644
- They'd love to make a connection.
- And you think they will?

761
01:25:06,027 --> 01:25:09,988
l think it's time
the whole thing went away.

762
01:25:09,988 --> 01:25:13,451
- lf that's what you think.
- l think so.

763
01:25:15,436 --> 01:25:19,779
Then it should go away.
lt never happened.

764
01:25:21,228 --> 01:25:23,115
Yes, sir.

765
01:25:24,556 --> 01:25:28,069
Well...it's possible.

766
01:25:28,069 --> 01:25:33,190
lt would be easier if you told me whose
system you wanted me to break into.

767
01:25:33,190 --> 01:25:35,244
- Morning, Dr Ryan.
- Morning.

768
01:25:55,917 --> 01:25:58,535
We're way beyond birthdays now.

769
01:25:59,469 --> 01:26:03,746
l am going to have to write
a special program here.

770
01:26:14,093 --> 01:26:17,868
OK, sweetheart, let's get to work.

771
01:26:18,766 --> 01:26:20,588
Fine, good.

772
01:26:21,965 --> 01:26:25,544
Yes... Here we go.

773
01:27:20,527 --> 01:27:23,397
Reciprocity. What's that?

774
01:27:35,760 --> 01:27:38,510
l forgot to tell you, after you get the code,

775
01:27:38,510 --> 01:27:43,341
wait until he's off his system
before you log on. He will know.

776
01:27:43,341 --> 01:27:45,774
Jesus, Petey, it's too late.

777
01:27:45,774 --> 01:27:48,237
Oh, my God...

778
01:28:17,617 --> 01:28:19,210
Cutter...

779
01:28:33,297 --> 01:28:37,454
- Bob, Jack Ryan here.
- Good morning, Jack.

780
01:28:37,937 --> 01:28:41,799
Listen, maybe we got off to a bad start.

781
01:28:42,546 --> 01:28:46,888
lf we're going to work together,
we should get to know each other.

782
01:28:46,888 --> 01:28:51,052
Do you play tennis?
Tennis? Do you play tennis?

783
01:28:51,052 --> 01:28:55,440
- Yeah, l play tennis.
- How about we get together?

784
01:28:55,440 --> 01:28:58,766
Next week?
Maybe an hour before we start work?

785
01:29:05,618 --> 01:29:07,593
- Jack?
- Yeah.

786
01:29:08,242 --> 01:29:12,552
Computer theft is a serious crime.

787
01:29:15,634 --> 01:29:18,798
So are crimes against the Constitution.

788
01:29:20,339 --> 01:29:22,313
Son of a bitch!

789
01:29:33,715 --> 01:29:35,624
Son of a bitch!

790
01:29:39,635 --> 01:29:40,977
Come on, come on.

791
01:29:44,147 --> 01:29:45,740
Clark...

792
01:30:20,500 --> 01:30:22,093
You're going to jail, pal.

793
01:30:23,573 --> 01:30:27,151
What is that?
What do you think you have there?

794
01:30:27,151 --> 01:30:28,843
You broke the law.

795
01:30:30,004 --> 01:30:33,801
You are such a Boy Scout.

796
01:30:33,801 --> 01:30:37,235
Look at you.
You see everything in black and white.

797
01:30:37,235 --> 01:30:41,194
No, not black and white, Ritter.
Right and wrong!

798
01:30:41,194 --> 01:30:45,707
- You see! There you go again.
- Why was l kept out of it?

799
01:30:45,707 --> 01:30:49,008
You weren't, you're neck deep in it.
You went before Congress.

800
01:30:49,008 --> 01:30:51,923
You got the money for it.
You lied under oath...

801
01:30:51,923 --> 01:30:56,689
- l never lied to Congress!
- You told them no troops.

802
01:30:56,689 --> 01:31:00,115
- There are troops!
- You know l didn't know that.

803
01:31:00,115 --> 01:31:05,711
No. l have no recollection of that.
That's the term you have to learn.

804
01:31:05,711 --> 01:31:09,739
- Who authorised this?
- Sure, they will ask you that.

805
01:31:09,739 --> 01:31:14,449
- Who authorised this?
- l have no recollection...Senator.

806
01:31:19,382 --> 01:31:23,572
l did not sign up for somebody's
bullshit political agenda.

807
01:31:23,572 --> 01:31:27,531
Who authorised this? Cutter?

808
01:31:27,531 --> 01:31:31,051
Cutter couldn't tie his shoes
without permission.

809
01:31:35,319 --> 01:31:38,635
- lf l go down, you're going with me.
- Wrong again.

810
01:31:38,635 --> 01:31:42,189
l have an autographed
''Get Out of Jail Free'' card.

811
01:31:44,086 --> 01:31:48,210
''The President authorises
the Deputy Director ClA, Robert Ritter,

812
01:31:48,210 --> 01:31:53,590
''to conduct Operation Reciprocity
including all support necessary.

813
01:31:53,590 --> 01:32:00,046
''This operation is deemed important
to the national security of the US.''

814
01:32:02,007 --> 01:32:06,317
You don't have one of these,
do you, Jack?

815
01:32:15,095 --> 01:32:19,917
Grey! The world's grey, Jack!

816
01:32:50,968 --> 01:32:55,856
You have any idea how l am going to
get out of this mess?

817
01:32:55,856 --> 01:32:58,992
Absolutely none.

818
01:33:07,321 --> 01:33:10,998
Yeah. This is he.

819
01:33:14,809 --> 01:33:16,435
When?

820
01:33:20,922 --> 01:33:21,642
James?

821
01:33:24,506 --> 01:33:26,644
Thank you.

822
01:33:26,644 --> 01:33:34,131
Admiral James Greer devoted his life
to his country and his family.

823
01:33:34,131 --> 01:33:38,259
Giving selflessly
of both his wisdom and his love.

824
01:33:39,450 --> 01:33:43,127
He served his country
for more than 50 years.

825
01:33:43,127 --> 01:33:48,276
Enlisting in the Navy at 17.
Graduating from the Academy.

826
01:33:48,276 --> 01:33:51,890
Achieving three stars for his flag.

827
01:33:51,890 --> 01:33:55,636
He lived through tumultuous events
in his country's life.

828
01:33:55,636 --> 01:34:00,025
He participated in them.
He made them clearer to the rest of us,

829
01:34:00,025 --> 01:34:06,352
with his knowledge, his honesty,
his integrity and his courage.

830
01:34:15,131 --> 01:34:16,822
l can't see them, but l know they're there.

831
01:34:17,626 --> 01:34:20,823
Five kilometres due east
from your position.

832
01:34:25,531 --> 01:34:28,914
Keep pushing forward. We will trap them.

833
01:34:28,914 --> 01:34:32,247
Never was he deluded
into thinking that one man...

834
01:34:33,180 --> 01:34:35,514
...could solve the ills of the world.

835
01:34:35,514 --> 01:34:40,182
Always the soldier, on the battlefields
of the South Pacific, Korea...

836
01:34:40,182 --> 01:34:44,821
...Vietnam and Washington,
he fought as part of a unit...

837
01:34:45,436 --> 01:34:47,224
... to preserve the ideals...

838
01:34:47,224 --> 01:34:48,729
Knife, this is Variable.

839
01:34:48,729 --> 01:34:50,714
...of his nation.

840
01:34:50,714 --> 01:34:53,723
Knife! This is Variable. Over.

841
01:34:54,652 --> 01:34:58,581
To the refuge of the earth,
we entrust our friend's body.

842
01:34:59,036 --> 01:35:03,259
To the protection of our God
in Heaven, we entrust his soul.

843
01:35:03,259 --> 01:35:07,795
To ourselves, we entrust his spirit...

844
01:35:07,795 --> 01:35:11,477
...and the principles he lived by.

845
01:35:11,477 --> 01:35:13,499
We're going to miss you, James.

846
01:35:35,389 --> 01:35:36,982
Variable, this is Knife, over.

847
01:35:38,269 --> 01:35:41,236
Variable, this is Knife, over.

848
01:35:41,236 --> 01:35:44,754
Variable, l am not receiving.
We are under heavy attack.

849
01:35:44,754 --> 01:35:48,057
Need air support, over.

850
01:36:08,542 --> 01:36:12,087
Variable, this is Knife, over! Switch!

851
01:36:43,327 --> 01:36:47,157
Variable, this is Knife!
Where the hell are you?!

852
01:37:07,776 --> 01:37:11,998
On behalf of a grateful nation,
our condolences.

853
01:37:11,998 --> 01:37:15,226
- He was a very great patriot.
- Thank you.

854
01:37:52,385 --> 01:37:56,541
- Hello?
- Jean Fowler for Dr Jack Ryan.

855
01:37:56,541 --> 01:38:00,001
Jack? You have got to hear this.

856
01:38:00,001 --> 01:38:02,495
Picked it up this morning.

857
01:38:02,495 --> 01:38:08,374
Variable, this is Knife.
We are under attack, need air support.

858
01:38:08,374 --> 01:38:11,611
Variable, this is Knife,
where the hell are you?

859
01:38:12,258 --> 01:38:15,160
Jack, what do you want me
to do with this?

860
01:38:16,129 --> 01:38:20,505
Make a copy, Jean. Make ten copies.

861
01:38:20,505 --> 01:38:23,488
Get them to me
as quick as you can. Thanks.

862
01:38:26,017 --> 01:38:30,174
Jesus. They're going to leave
those guys down there.

863
01:39:11,747 --> 01:39:17,344
He's on American 915.
He will be in Bogota 7.50 p.m.

864
01:39:29,156 --> 01:39:30,978
-Yeah?
- lt's Ritter.

865
01:39:30,978 --> 01:39:34,784
- Where the fuck have you been?
- We have a problem.

866
01:39:34,784 --> 01:39:37,566
We have got a disaster!
l can't get through to my men.

867
01:39:38,148 --> 01:39:41,312
We had to shut down the satellite link.

868
01:39:43,076 --> 01:39:45,345
- Clark?
- You had to what?

869
01:39:47,172 --> 01:39:52,889
lt's Ryan. He found out everything.
He threatened to tell Congress

870
01:39:53,188 --> 01:39:56,003
if we didn't shut down the operation.

871
01:39:56,003 --> 01:40:01,467
OK. lt's shut down. Just give me
some air and my men are out of there.

872
01:40:02,757 --> 01:40:09,315
Clark, maybe you're not hearing me.
There is no air. We are shut down.

873
01:40:10,564 --> 01:40:13,980
l am on a plane. l am going to kill him.

874
01:40:15,205 --> 01:40:16,514
Ritter?

875
01:40:19,045 --> 01:40:21,380
He's coming to you.

876
01:40:21,797 --> 01:40:25,343
American Airlines at 19.50
with no security.

877
01:40:25,343 --> 01:40:29,885
- Who is this?
- National Security Advisor Cutter.

878
01:40:29,885 --> 01:40:32,509
Once Ryan's gone, we're back on line.

879
01:40:33,030 --> 01:40:34,786
You understand?

880
01:40:36,166 --> 01:40:38,206
Yes, sir.

881
01:41:55,944 --> 01:41:57,253
Clark...

882
01:41:57,253 --> 01:41:59,074
- Jesus!
- Get in the van.

883
01:41:59,074 --> 01:42:03,615
- Don't do this, l came to find you.
- You found me. Get in.

884
01:42:07,816 --> 01:42:09,442
Behind the wheel.

885
01:42:10,888 --> 01:42:12,295
Clark...

886
01:42:13,704 --> 01:42:15,362
Drive.

887
01:42:42,217 --> 01:42:44,705
- Ritter.
- Ryan's dead.

888
01:42:46,697 --> 01:42:47,697
How?

889
01:42:48,841 --> 01:42:51,841
l killed him. Turn the satellite back on.

890
01:42:55,209 --> 01:42:59,781
You said get rid of Ryan
and we're back in business, right?

891
01:43:23,946 --> 01:43:25,888
What the hell are you doing here?

892
01:43:28,202 --> 01:43:31,236
l came to help you get those guys out.

893
01:43:32,811 --> 01:43:35,298
What can you do to help me?

894
01:43:40,747 --> 01:43:43,594
What do you need?

895
01:43:43,594 --> 01:43:45,064
A helicopter.

896
01:43:47,243 --> 01:43:49,130
A helicopter.

897
01:43:57,931 --> 01:43:59,208
No, thank you.

898
01:44:02,059 --> 01:44:04,994
- ls this ''Happy Hour''?
- lt's always ''Happy Hour''.

899
01:44:04,994 --> 01:44:08,676
- Your pilot owns this joint?
- He lives here.

900
01:44:14,284 --> 01:44:15,560
Here he is.

901
01:44:26,476 --> 01:44:30,884
Morning. l am here to rent the Huey.

902
01:44:30,884 --> 01:44:35,013
Sorry, we don't rent it any more.
But it is for sale.

903
01:44:36,620 --> 01:44:38,409
How much is it?

904
01:44:39,756 --> 01:44:42,058
Two million dollars.

905
01:44:47,628 --> 01:44:50,149
My pilot and l would
have to do a test flight.

906
01:44:50,149 --> 01:44:53,164
Of course.
You just have to leave a deposit.

907
01:44:54,988 --> 01:44:56,744
How much is that?

908
01:44:56,744 --> 01:44:58,337
Two million dollars.

909
01:45:03,853 --> 01:45:06,668
Would you take a company cheque?

910
01:45:13,325 --> 01:45:14,754
Yes.

911
01:45:22,381 --> 01:45:25,927
- Here we go.
- Big son of a bitch, ain't she?

912
01:45:28,077 --> 01:45:32,168
- Do you have any time in this type?
- Nine o'clock.

913
01:45:41,838 --> 01:45:47,751
- Get out of my chopper.
- No. My chopper. Let's go.

914
01:46:07,438 --> 01:46:10,438
Their last communication put them here.

915
01:46:11,663 --> 01:46:16,519
The closest extraction point is here.
ln this gorge.

916
01:46:17,390 --> 01:46:19,049
l got it.

917
01:46:38,192 --> 01:46:41,388
- ls that a body down there?
- Yes.

918
01:46:43,344 --> 01:46:46,726
- One of ours?
- One of mine.

919
01:46:50,128 --> 01:46:54,187
Find a place to set her down.
We will look for the others.

920
01:47:36,049 --> 01:47:40,719
Nowhere to run to. No place to hide.

921
01:47:40,719 --> 01:47:46,348
Blood trails everywhere.
They all lead to the river.

922
01:47:58,449 --> 01:48:02,410
These are the falls we saw from the air.

923
01:48:02,410 --> 01:48:06,026
The bodies should be
about 50 metres down.

924
01:48:17,843 --> 01:48:22,577
You left us!
You left us with no support at all!

925
01:48:22,577 --> 01:48:26,863
You left us out to dry!
You son of a bitch!

926
01:48:29,522 --> 01:48:32,817
- lt's not his fault.
- Whose fault is it?

927
01:48:34,738 --> 01:48:36,015
lt's my fault.

928
01:48:41,363 --> 01:48:43,337
lt's my fault.

929
01:48:54,932 --> 01:48:58,707
l was on point
when the last attack came.

930
01:48:59,667 --> 01:49:01,707
Over a mile away.

931
01:49:02,867 --> 01:49:05,103
By the time l got back it was over.

932
01:49:06,452 --> 01:49:09,485
They were taken to Captain Rosso.

933
01:49:10,611 --> 01:49:13,230
The others?

934
01:49:13,230 --> 01:49:15,021
l buried them.

935
01:49:23,764 --> 01:49:25,553
Road to the town.

936
01:49:25,553 --> 01:49:28,945
They loaded the prisoners here.
Blood everywhere.

937
01:49:28,945 --> 01:49:32,818
- God knows where they are now.
- Escobedo knows.

938
01:49:32,818 --> 01:49:36,145
What are you going to do?
Knock on his door?

939
01:49:42,517 --> 01:49:47,274
Morning. l'd like to see Ernesto
Escobedo. l don't have an appointment.

940
01:50:00,277 --> 01:50:01,027
OK.

941
01:50:04,021 --> 01:50:05,810
Hands up.

942
01:50:06,485 --> 01:50:08,557
Hands up!

943
01:50:09,845 --> 01:50:11,700
Wallet.

944
01:50:16,309 --> 01:50:17,870
lt's a tape recorder.

945
01:50:22,422 --> 01:50:24,396
He's in.

946
01:50:27,670 --> 01:50:30,288
Bird, this is Variable, over.

947
01:50:31,958 --> 01:50:35,602
Bird, this is Variable, over.

948
01:50:51,318 --> 01:50:54,766
Dr Ryan... Come in.

949
01:51:08,183 --> 01:51:11,728
Sit down. What can l do for you?

950
01:51:13,079 --> 01:51:18,862
l didn't know who else to turn to.
l have a problem.

951
01:51:19,735 --> 01:51:23,281
An associate of mine,
a coffee buyer and his assistant

952
01:51:23,281 --> 01:51:26,131
were on a business trip in this area.

953
01:51:26,131 --> 01:51:29,874
They disappeared yesterday.
l am very concerned.

954
01:51:29,874 --> 01:51:32,244
Coffee buyer?

955
01:51:32,244 --> 01:51:34,961
lt's very important to me to find them.

956
01:51:34,961 --> 01:51:38,292
Coffee buying is becoming
a dangerous business.

957
01:51:39,544 --> 01:51:44,498
Yes. Well, it was for Peter Hardin.

958
01:51:46,872 --> 01:51:50,353
- Who?
- He was a client of Lindo Coffee.

959
01:51:50,353 --> 01:51:55,277
- Lindo Coffee has many clients.
- You must have heard of this one.

960
01:51:55,277 --> 01:51:58,864
He owed your company
a great deal of money.

961
01:51:58,864 --> 01:52:02,993
l will have to talk to Accounting about that.

962
01:52:04,280 --> 01:52:06,549
650 million dollars.

963
01:52:09,561 --> 01:52:11,700
And change.

964
01:52:13,081 --> 01:52:18,132
Are you offering to help me
with the collection of an unpaid debt?

965
01:52:18,132 --> 01:52:21,079
- No.
- What are you offering?

966
01:52:22,489 --> 01:52:27,061
A trade. Felix Cortez has sold you out.

967
01:52:27,061 --> 01:52:31,316
He will murder you and your family,
and take over the cartel.

968
01:52:31,316 --> 01:52:33,270
Where's my tape recorder?

969
01:52:39,609 --> 01:52:41,333
Play the tape.

970
01:53:13,787 --> 01:53:15,412
Let's move.

971
01:53:44,123 --> 01:53:47,385
l'd like you to meet
my new friend, Dr Ryan.

972
01:53:47,385 --> 01:53:50,646
A doctor? Why? ls somebody sick?

973
01:54:03,708 --> 01:54:05,115
What does he want?

974
01:54:07,195 --> 01:54:10,578
The safe return of his associates.

975
01:54:10,578 --> 01:54:14,774
And what does he offer us in return?

976
01:54:14,774 --> 01:54:15,774
You.

977
01:54:22,876 --> 01:54:26,870
Whatever this man has told you is a lie.
He lies for a living.

978
01:54:26,870 --> 01:54:31,412
He's in the intelligence business.
You're in the intelligence business!

979
01:54:37,724 --> 01:54:40,441
You have taken care of the little fish.

980
01:54:40,441 --> 01:54:42,743
l will take care of the one that got away.

981
01:54:43,261 --> 01:54:47,898
Once Escobedo is gone,
l will be in a position to help you.

982
01:54:47,898 --> 01:54:52,022
So, the question is...

983
01:54:53,277 --> 01:54:55,513
...what am l supposed to do with you?

984
01:54:58,974 --> 01:55:01,624
l guess l am supposed to
kill you with this bat!

985
01:55:10,174 --> 01:55:12,028
Get up.

986
01:55:16,542 --> 01:55:20,732
Dramatic seizures.
Drastic reductions, no more violence...

987
01:55:20,732 --> 01:55:22,901
You will have your victory.

988
01:55:24,574 --> 01:55:27,160
ln return for what?

989
01:56:05,151 --> 01:56:07,006
- Where are they?
- They're here.

990
01:56:09,727 --> 01:56:13,502
The American killed Ernesto! Let's go!

991
01:56:59,712 --> 01:57:01,851
Bird to Variable. Over.

992
01:57:14,754 --> 01:57:19,260
Bird, this is Variable.
Where the hell are you?

993
01:57:19,260 --> 01:57:22,873
l am cruising about five klicks
south of the village.

994
01:57:23,617 --> 01:57:28,124
- Stay there. l will get back to you.
- Roger that.

995
01:57:39,426 --> 01:57:41,760
- No one.
- The prisoners!

996
01:58:26,595 --> 01:58:29,214
Come on, guys. Let's go, son.

997
01:58:30,787 --> 01:58:32,576
We're going home, boys.

998
01:59:43,333 --> 01:59:45,788
Pick us up at the Lindo Coffee factory.

999
02:01:18,440 --> 02:01:22,270
Not only can l expose you
to the press, so can the soldiers.

1000
02:01:22,270 --> 02:01:28,769
Do you want to take your chances
with the courts and the reporters?

1001
02:01:28,769 --> 02:01:32,798
To end the political career
of your commander-in-chief?

1002
02:02:15,561 --> 02:02:17,733
Let's go!

1003
02:02:43,914 --> 02:02:47,460
Get your asses in here!
Come on, we got to go!

1004
02:02:50,282 --> 02:02:51,242
Come on!

1005
02:02:58,666 --> 02:03:01,252
Hold it! We wait for Ryan!

1006
02:03:01,252 --> 02:03:02,881
Yeah? We're out of here!

1007
02:03:09,995 --> 02:03:12,810
Set it down! He's down there!

1008
02:03:24,908 --> 02:03:26,850
Come on!

1009
02:03:44,716 --> 02:03:46,277
l have got you!

1010
02:03:53,004 --> 02:03:54,947
Chavez, cover me!

1011
02:04:03,788 --> 02:04:05,730
Your hand. Give me your hand!

1012
02:05:10,094 --> 02:05:12,964
The President will see you now.

1013
02:05:24,782 --> 02:05:27,630
Jack! l am glad you're here.

1014
02:05:29,039 --> 02:05:32,901
Sit down. Can l get you anything?

1015
02:05:32,901 --> 02:05:33,651
No.

1016
02:05:35,599 --> 02:05:39,723
- Come on, sit down.
- l would prefer to stand, sir.

1017
02:05:42,063 --> 02:05:47,976
Some things have gone on here
that l am just becoming aware of.

1018
02:05:47,976 --> 02:05:52,202
l was kept in the dark, as you were,
for a very long time.

1019
02:05:52,202 --> 02:05:55,498
- Troubling things.
- Yeah.

1020
02:05:55,498 --> 02:05:59,820
Now we have to sort them out,
figure out who's responsible for what.

1021
02:05:59,820 --> 02:06:03,628
And what to do about it.
And we have to do it delicately,

1022
02:06:03,628 --> 02:06:06,509
otherwise people might
get the wrong idea.

1023
02:06:07,792 --> 02:06:09,068
We have to lie.

1024
02:06:11,088 --> 02:06:15,278
- Did l say that?
- No, you didn't.

1025
02:06:15,278 --> 02:06:18,921
- You're upset.
- l am upset.

1026
02:06:18,921 --> 02:06:24,239
lt's understandable. Do you mind
if l give you a bit of advice?

1027
02:06:24,239 --> 02:06:26,767
Of course, you know this. You're smart.

1028
02:06:26,767 --> 02:06:30,244
Never make important decisions
while you're upset.

1029
02:06:31,184 --> 02:06:36,335
You did. American soldiers and
innocent civilians are dead because of it.

1030
02:06:36,335 --> 02:06:40,523
- l never ordered any...
- Don't you play that game with me!

1031
02:06:40,523 --> 02:06:44,431
Do not dishonour their memories
by pretending you didn't know!

1032
02:06:44,431 --> 02:06:48,008
- How dare you lecture me!
- How dare you, sir!

1033
02:06:48,008 --> 02:06:52,138
How dare you come here and bark at me
like some little junkyard dog!

1034
02:06:52,138 --> 02:06:55,338
l am the President of the United States!

1035
02:06:59,217 --> 02:07:01,967
lt gives me no pleasure to do it, sir.

1036
02:07:02,929 --> 02:07:05,929
As acting Deputy Director
of lntelligence, it is my duty

1037
02:07:05,929 --> 02:07:09,840
to report this matter
to the Senate Oversight Committee.

1038
02:07:14,673 --> 02:07:20,173
- You're not going to do that.
- l am not?

1039
02:07:22,546 --> 02:07:26,158
You have got yourself
a chip in the big game now.

1040
02:07:27,538 --> 02:07:32,906
You're going to save that for a time
when your own ass is on the line.

1041
02:07:33,459 --> 02:07:36,328
And then you're going to pull it out.

1042
02:07:36,328 --> 02:07:40,524
And l am going to cash it in for you.
Right?

1043
02:07:42,514 --> 02:07:45,809
l don't think l have anything more
to say to you, sir.

1044
02:07:47,155 --> 02:07:52,370
The country can't afford another
scandal, Jack. To protect itself,

1045
02:07:52,370 --> 02:07:57,997
it won't allow another deception
that goes all the way to the top.

1046
02:07:57,997 --> 02:08:01,993
You will take the blame.
Cutter and Ritter will take some too,

1047
02:08:01,993 --> 02:08:05,262
but it will only amount to
a slap on the wrist.

1048
02:08:05,262 --> 02:08:09,257
Then 20,000 dollars an hour
on the lecture circuit.

1049
02:08:10,387 --> 02:08:14,316
The rest of the blame will fall on Greer.

1050
02:08:14,316 --> 02:08:18,029
Oh yeah, you will take him down with you.

1051
02:08:18,029 --> 02:08:20,203
You will destroy his reputation.

1052
02:08:20,788 --> 02:08:26,155
But that's as far as it will go.
The old Potomac two-step, Jack.

1053
02:08:28,980 --> 02:08:32,526
l am sorry, Mr President, l don't dance.

1054
02:08:55,028 --> 02:08:57,036
Ryan, have you got a minute?

1055
02:08:57,036 --> 02:08:57,786
No.

1056
02:08:59,893 --> 02:09:02,576
We need to talk!

1057
02:09:02,576 --> 02:09:04,628
Ryan!

1058
02:09:27,925 --> 02:09:33,359
The Committee will come to order.
The chair will now call Dr John Ryan.

1059
02:09:53,430 --> 02:09:59,059
Dr Ryan, thank you for appearing
before the Committee today.

1060
02:09:59,830 --> 02:10:02,416
Please stand and raise your right hand.

1061
02:10:06,134 --> 02:10:09,931
Do you solemnly swear
that the testimony you're about to give

1062
02:10:09,931 --> 02:10:14,259
is the whole truth and nothing
but the truth, so help you God?

1063
02:10:17,399 --> 02:10:19,253
l do.

1064
02:10:20,343 --> 02:10:24,402
Dr Ryan, you may consider yourself
under oath. Please be seated.

